com.qualcomm.hardware.hitechnic

Class HiTechnicNxtController

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.I2cControllerPortDeviceImpl
      • com.qualcomm.hardware.hitechnic.HiTechnicNxtController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Engagable, HardwareDevice, I2cControllerPortDevice, RobotArmingStateNotifier.Callback
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HiTechnicNxtDcMotorController, HiTechnicNxtServoController

    public abstract class HiTechnicNxtController
extends I2cControllerPortDeviceImpl
implements Engagable, HardwareDevice
    HiTechnicNxtController serves as a common implementation base for legacy motor and servo controllers. Its primary functionality is to keep track of user's intent as to whether or not a controller should be engaged with its underlying I2cDevice, and manage the state transitions associated with doing so.
